HTC has opened pre-orders for the Vive Pro VR headset. The device is on sale for $799 and will start shipping in April, said the company. The Vive Pro sports a redesigned chassis and improved display resolution compared to the original headset. The new head-mounted display also includes redesigned ergonomics, and features improved weight balance and adjustment options. HTC has also added a pair of detachable headphones to the Vive Pro, removing the need to use standalone headphones with the device. The Vive Pro boasts a 78% increased pixel count and 37% increased pixel density over the standard HTC Vive, delivering a sharper image via twoÂ 1,440 x 1,600 AMOLED panels.